# Use React, Apollo and Tailwind/HeroUI

- For our UI components, we are using HeroUI, which we should use for all react components where possible (avoid implementing our own components unless necessary).

- Always use Typescript for react components! `.tsx`

- Here our tailwind configuration: [tailwind.config.js](mdc:config/tailwind.config.js)

- If you need to reference the overall layout that wraps each page, [Layout.tsx](mdc:app/javascript/layouts/Layout.tsx)

- When building forms and inputs, we may want to remember state using inertia `import { useRemember } from '@inertiajs/react'`

- When creating HeroUI <Button /> components, be sure to use `onPress` instead of `onClick`, as they have deprecated `onClick` in favor of using `onPress`

- [NAVIGATION.md](mdc:app/javascript/docs/NAVIGATION.md) - Best practices for SPA navigation



